According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Weapons Bore (Laser, Optical) Corrosion & Fatigue Inspection Scope Market was valued at USD 142.6 million in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 148.3 million in 2026 to USD 214.9 million by 2034, registering a CAGR of 4.7% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady growth as military organizations worldwide invest in advanced non-destructive inspection technologies to improve weapon reliability, extend barrel life, and enhance mission readiness. Growing defense modernization initiatives, condition-based maintenance programs, and increasing demand for precision diagnostics are driving the adoption of laser and optical bore inspection systems across global armed forces.
